        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 8:12PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 812 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Texola, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sayre, Erick, Carter, Texola, and Delhi.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
